## Migration Steps

### Step 1 — Install the missing dependency
```powershell
cd C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg
pnpm --filter @foodgenie/web add lucide-react
```

### Step 2 — Copy the UI components
```powershell
# Copy the component library
Copy-Item "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg-gemini\packages\web\src\components\ui\index.tsx" `
          "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\components\ui\index.tsx"
```

### Step 3 — Copy the mock data layer
```powershell
# Create the data directory and copy
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\data"
Copy-Item "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg-gemini\packages\web\src\data\mockData.ts" `
          "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\data\mockData.ts"
```

### Step 4 — Copy all page components
```powershell
# Copy all pages
Copy-Item "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg-gemini\packages\web\src\pages\*.tsx" `
          "C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\pages\"
```

### Step 5 — Create the barrel re-export files
The page components import from `'./components'` and `'./data'` (relative paths from when they were at the src root). You need shim files:

**Create `C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\pages\components.ts`:**
```ts
export { Button, Card, Badge, Label, Input, TextArea, Checkbox, RangeInput, Modal, FacebookIcon, Layout } from '../components/ui';
```

**Create `C:\Users\kirkm\Projects\fg\packages\web\src\pages\data.ts`:**
```ts
export * from '../data/mockData';
```

### Step 6 — Choose your App.tsx approach

> [!IMPORTANT]
> fg uses `react-router-dom` (URL-based routing) while fg-gemini uses state-based routing (`useState`). You must choose one approach.

**Option A: State-based routing (match fg-gemini exactly)**
Replace [App.tsx](file:///C:/Users/kirkm/Projects/fg/packages/web/src/App.tsx) and [main.tsx](file:///C:/Users/kirkm/Projects/fg/packages/web/src/main.tsx) with the same files we created for fg-gemini (remove `BrowserRouter`).

**Option B: Convert to react-router-dom routes (recommended for fg)**
Keep fg's `BrowserRouter` setup and wire the pages into proper `<Route>` elements. This is better long-term but requires you to adjust how pages navigate (replace `onChangeView('recipes')` calls with `useNavigate('/recipes')` from react-router-dom).

### Step 7 — Align styling

**Option A: Keep fg's font/color scheme** (no changes needed to Tailwind config).
The pages use Tailwind's built-in colors (`emerald`, `slate`, `blue`, etc.) more than the custom `primary` palette, so they'll look fine with either config.

**Option B: Match fg-gemini's look exactly**
- Replace [index.css](file:///C:/Users/kirkm/Projects/fg/packages/web/src/index.css) with fg-gemini's version (Inter font)
- Replace [tailwind.config.js](file:///C:/Users/kirkm/Projects/fg/packages/web/tailwind.config.js) with fg-gemini's version
- Remove the Google Fonts `<link>` tags from [index.html](file:///C:/Users/kirkm/Projects/fg/packages/web/index.html)

